4 HJR___ RECOGNIZING MARCH 3, 2026, AS KAPPA ALPHA PSI
5 FRATERNITY®, INCORPORATED, DAY AT THE ALABAMA STATE CAPITOL
6 AND COMMENDING KAPPA ALPHA PSI FRATERNITY®, INCORPORATED, ON
7 THE OCCASION OF ITS 115TH ANNIVERSARY.
8
9 WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity®, Incorporated,
10 was founded on January 5, 1911, on the campus of Indiana
11 University in Bloomington, Indiana; and
12 WHEREAS, guided by its noble fundamental purpose,
13 "Achievement in Every Field of Human Endeavor," the
14 fraternity has, for more than a century, cultivated
15 leadership, scholarship, and service, a legacy first
16 exemplified by its 10 distinguished founders, the majority
17 of whom earned collegiate degrees and achieved notable
18 success in their respective professions; and
19 WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity®, Incorporated,
20 has grown to include more than 250,000 members worldwide,
21 with over 700 undergraduate, alumni, and international
22 chapters, forming a powerful global network committed to
23 excellence and brotherhood; and
24 WHEREAS, through the Kappa Alpha Psi Foundation, the
25 fraternity sponsors impactful programs that promote
26 community service, social welfare, youth mentorship, and
27 academic scholarship, thereby strengthening communities
28 across the nation and abroad; and
Page 1

across the nation and abroad; and
HJR150 INTRODUCED
29 WHEREAS, the five core objectives of Kappa Alpha Psi
30 Fraternity®, Incorporated, are to unite college men of
31 culture, patriotism, and honor in a lifelong bond of
32 fraternity; to encourage honorable achievement in every
33 field of human endeavor; to promote the spiritual, social,
34 intellectual, and moral welfare of its members; to assist in
35 the aims and purposes of colleges and universities; and to
36 inspire service in the public interest; and
37 WHEREAS, the visionary founders sought to shape "a
38 group personality unique in the annals of college
39 Greek-letter organizations around the ideal of achievement,"
40 a vision that continues to distinguish the fraternity as a
41 beacon of leadership, integrity, and accomplishment; and
42 WHEREAS, five esteemed members of Kappa Alpha Psi
43 Fraternity®, Incorporated, presently serve with distinction
44 in the Alabama House of Representatives: Minority Leader
45 Anthony Daniels; House Black Caucus Chairman A.J.
46 McCampbell; Ranking Minority Member Thomas "Action" Jackson;
47 Representative Patrick Sellers; and Representative Travis
48 Hendrix; now therefore,
49 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
50 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we proudly recognize March
51 3, 2026, as Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity®, Incorporated, Day
52 at the Alabama State Capitol and extend our highest
53 commendation and heartfelt congratulations to Kappa Alpha
54 Psi Fraternity®, Incorporated, on the celebration of its
55 115th Anniversary, expressing our deepest admiration and
